id: pm-rrjv
title: 2026-05-02 Comprehensive PM CLI Audit
description: "Full audit covering code quality, performance, telemetry analysis, SDK review, search, calendar, and extensibility."
type: Epic
status: open
priority: 0
tags[4]: audit,dogfood,"milestone:0",pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-01T22:37:48.560Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-01T22:39:38.076Z"
author: audit-agent
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T22:39:12.421Z",audit-agent,"AUDIT RESULTS (2026-05-02): SECURITY: PASS - No credentials in source (check-secrets.mjs confirms). Private IPs in 2 .toon files are audit artifacts only. Telemetry not documented in public docs. DOGFOOD: PASS - Full lifecycle works (init, create, claim, update, files, notes, comments, close, release). Error guidance is excellent (structured: What/Why/Required/Examples/NextSteps). TOON output is token-efficient. JSON output is machine-parseable. Calendar: 4 views x 3 formats working. SEARCH: PASS - Hybrid mode (keyword+semantic) working. Score 1.0 for exact-match queries. Ollama qwen3-embedding:0.6b + LanceDB integrated correctly. 644 vectorized entries for 625 items. CODE QUALITY: toErrorMessage duplicated in 5 files, toNonEmptyString in 5+ files, nowIso duplicated. 15 dead facade files in src/. main.ts is 237KB monolith but well-structured. TypeScript strict mode passes clean. PERFORMANCE: list P50=732ms P95=2576ms for 625 items. search P50=1544ms P95=9606ms. health P95=7783ms. Startup=600ms. TELEMETRY: 32333 events from 1356 installs. Stack healthy (9 containers). 21 events stuck with timeout. SDK: Comprehensive (117 type exports, 9 capabilities, defineExtension helper). Extensions work."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T22:39:30.122Z",audit-agent,"Audit methodology: (1) Security scan via check-secrets.mjs + grep for credentials (2) Sandbox dogfood in /tmp with full lifecycle exercise (3) Code quality analysis via grep for duplicated patterns (4) SDK review of exports + extension examples (5) Search verification with semantic queries against real items (6) Calendar test of all 4 views x 3 formats (7) Telemetry Postgres analysis from remote stack (8) Performance profiling via time command + telemetry P50/P95 data"
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T22:39:21.151Z",audit-agent,"Telemetry data from real users is the most valuable signal for prioritization. The top 3 error messages (no update flags, invalid status closed, undefined ID) each suggest specific UX improvements that would prevent confusion. Performance P95 data reveals search and health as the two highest-impact optimization targets."
